		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Criminal justice</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:352px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Cjsflowco.svg" class="image" title="United States criminal justice system flowchart."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/Cjsflowco.svg/350px-Cjsflowco.svg.png" width="350" height="213" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Cjsflowco.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
United States criminal justice system flowchart.</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="dablink">For the <a href="/wiki/BBC" title="BBC">BBC</a> TV Series, see <a href="/wiki/Criminal_Justice_(TV_series)" title="Criminal Justice (TV series)">Criminal Justice (TV series)</a>.</div>
<p><b>Criminal justice</b> is the system of practices and institutions of <a href="/wiki/Government" title="Government">governments</a> directed at upholding <a href="/wiki/Social_control" title="Social control">social control</a>, <a href="/wiki/Deterrence_(legal)" title="Deterrence (legal)">deterring</a> and mitigating <a href="/wiki/Crime" title="Crime">crime</a>, and sanctioning those who violate <a href="/wiki/Law" title="Law">laws</a> with criminal penalties and rehabilitation efforts.</p>
<p>The <a href="/wiki/Rights_of_the_accused" title="Rights of the accused">rights of the accused</a> are <a href="/wiki/Right" title="Right" class="mw-redirect">rights</a> that protect those accused of crime.</p>
